Also I was told that things have not changed compared to the last programme that I applied to do in 2019/2020, but I would like to be able to learn more so I can be able to help other people.

Being part of Afro Voices & Cook Writer eat I learnt new skills which came in handy both professionally and personally, for example the recipes we make in the food club are easy and more importantly delicious, this helped me when I and my team got an opportunity to cook for the Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS) delegation which included a President from one of the countries with the help of Afro Voices & Cook Writer Eat volunteers and members.

I am so grateful for the guidance which I received from Afro Voices & Cook Writer Eat.

We spend a lot of our time supporting the progress of identified promising leaders, writers and artists working for social justice in Sub-Saharan Africa. Collectively our names and our projects represent a wide variety of fields – from sustainability and agriculture to child health, education and to the arts – but all projects fall under 4 broad themes listed below. Together, we ambitiously and collaboratively are working to improve universal access to knowledge beyond just our own projects.
